title: pk_machine_gun
body:
The PK machine gun is a Soviet general purpose machine gun, introduced in 1961.

This tag is for the original, earlier production of the PK machine gun, before it was modernized with the [[PKM]] in 1969. It can be distinguished from the PKM by its long flash hider, half-fluted barrel (fluted up to the gas block), and smooth top cover.

Both the PK and PKM were superseded by the [[pkp_pecheneg|PKP Pecheneg]] in 2001.

title: pkm
body:
PKM, or Pulemyot Kalashnikova Modernizirovanniy (Machine gun, Kalashnikov, Modernized), is a Soviet and Russian general-purpose machine gun in service since 1969, itself a modernized version of the [[pk_machine_gun|early PK]] design from 1961. Most often depicted with wooden grip, skeleton stock, and 100-round box magazine. Unlike American light machine guns, the ammunition belt is fed from the right side using a non-disintegrating belt link. 

This modernized version can be distinguished from the original [[pk_machine_gun|PK]] by a shorter flash hider; smooth barrel (the earlier one had the first half of the barrel fluted); and a ribbed top cover.

This gun is slated to be replaced by the [[PKP_Pecheneg|PKP Pecheneg]]. The best way to differentiate between the PKM and the PKP is the position of the carry handle; the Pecheneg's carry handle is right above the barrel while the PKM's carry handle protrudes above the receiver.

title: talavera

Talavera is a Mexican pottery tradition from Puebla, Mexico. It features a distinct white base glaze with primarily blue accents but colors such as yellow, black, green, orange and mauve have also been used. Its production started in Puebla because of the quality of the natural clay found there. 

Majolica pottery was brought to Mexico by the Spanish in the first century of the colonial period.

title: trim_marks
body:
Trim marks, aka crop marks, are used to show where to physically crop the image after printing it.  This is used when the size of the final product doesn't quite match a standard paper size.

Additionally, the extra margin allows the artist to "bleed" color beyond it and ensure that mistakes in trimming do not ruin the final product.

The Japanese word is Tonbo (トンボ).  Unfortunately, this is also a homophone for [[dragonfly]] in Japanese, which is what most "Pixiv searches":http://www.pixiv.net/tags.php?tag=%E3%83%88%E3%83%B3%E3%83%9C will turn up.

title: zenkoku_seifuku_bishoujo_grand_prix
body:
An adult puzzle game/visual novel released by Lyceen in 1996, with a sequel series [i]Seigra '97[/i] released the very next year.  This work would also promote the creation of the [i]Find Love[/i] series of dating simulation games, starting with [i]Find Love:  Rhapsody[/i] released in 1999.

This game was one of the first to display nude women with pubic hair, though actual details of sexual organs were still left blank.  The game was divided into five "areas" covering different sectors of Japan (North, East, West, South and Middle), with seven girls of high school age allocated to each area.  Once the game was published, fans would vote on various characters; such tallies were noted on in illustration books that showed stills from the game published by 1998. Her glasses are gone and the general look of her outfit remains but in a bodysuit form, exposing her greatly [[breast expansion|enlarged]] [[large breasts|chest]], and the top some of her thighs, starting a little over where the torso begins and little over the middle of her thigh. The outfit itself is still primarily black and with white sections much like her previous form.

When she transforms, the only word needed to describe her is "psycho." Rei becomes extremely irrational, unreasonable, and overbearing. title: oinari-sama_(kemono_friends)
body:
A [i][[Kemono Friends]][/i] character.

Inari Ookami is the japanese deity of agriculture, rice, foxes and many other things. They are represented in many forms but none is technically correct.

Oinari-sama is a Cryptid Friend based on the fox aspect of the deity as well as the patron deity of the red foxes.

She is dressed in an all-white blazer uniform similar to [[ezo_red_fox (kemono_friends)|Ezo Red Fox]] and [[silver_fox (kemono_friends)|Silver Fox]] with bows on the blazer instead of buttons and a red bow to add a splash of color and to replace the other's neckties and scarves. She wears no pantyhose, instead prefering traditional tabi and geta with an extra ribbon tied around her left thigh. Obviously, she also has fox ears and tail, all-white except for the interior of her ears which are pink. A golden ring or ribbon surrounds her tail near the tip.

title: razgriz
body:
[i] "When history witnesses a great change, Razgriz reveals itself. First as a dark demon. As a demon, it uses its power to rain death upon the land, and then it dies. However, after a period of slumber, Razgriz returns. This time, as a great hero."[/i]

Mythical demon whose legend is told in [[ace_combat_5|Ace Combat 5: The Unsung War]]. 

Representing the duality of light and dark, the legend says that the Demon of Razgriz summoned a tempest that desecrated the land for seventy days, killing all those within, including the demon itself. However, after time passes, an old traveler comes to restore the land and bring new life to it, but when the traveler leaves, it announces that it too was Razgriz.

She later is adopted as the insignia of the aptly named Razgriz Squadron, otherwise called the "Ghosts of Razgriz" for their exceptional piloting skills and the fact that they [spoiler]fake their deaths after Hamilton, who was allied with the true antagonist, had deceived the Osean Air Defense Force into believing that Wardog Squadron were traitors.[/spoiler]

Use this tag when the Razgriz Squadron insignia is depicted or when an [[f-14_tomcat|F-14 Tomcat]] is deliberately using the black and red color scheme often associated with the Squadron.

title: help:array_syntax
body:
When searching by arrays, the following variations on search parameters can be used.

h5. Whitespace separated lists

These parameter variations use whitespace (spaces, tabs, linebreaks) as a separator for the array, regardless of whether the individual items are numbers or text. This is the default and has no qualifier.

h5. Array separated lists

These parameter variations use the URL array format to input the separate items. Is denoted with the qualifier "array".

[b]Example:[/b]

[code]
search[parameter1_include_any_array][]=foo&search[parameter1_include_any_array][]=bar
[/code]

The above sends the items as an array where it will end up as [code]["foo", "bar"][/code].

h5. Lowercase lists

These parameter variations apply a lowercase transformation to both the input and the record fields when making the comparisons. Is denoted with the qualifier "lower".

h5. Includes any

Will return all records that include any of the items from the array. Is denoted with the qualifier "include_any".

h5. Includes all

Will return all records that include all of the items from the array. Is denoted with the qualifier "include_all".

h5. Count

Searches using the count of items in the array. Uses the same parameter format as numbers (see [[Help:Number syntax]]).

h5. All parameter variations

For the following, [code]NAME[/code] is the name of the record field being searched for.

* [code]NAME_include_any[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_all[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_any_array[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_all_array[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_any_lower[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_all_lower[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_any_lower_array[/code]
* [code]NAME_include_all_lower_array[/code]
* [code]NAME_count[/code]

A lumberman in seclusion.
He got displaced to avoid the White Cape.
There is detachment beside his handsome look.

As the eldest child, Rand was demanded by family to set a good example and be a 'model man'. However, he dared not let anyone in the conservative Crossport find out he is Gyee.

He kept the identity secret, concerned about causing the family 'shame' and 'dishonor', maybe even threats of death. He would hang out at an underground Gyee bar and vent with fellow kindred spirits, but then White Capes raided the enclave and hung all Gyee captives on the town square, dubbing them minions of the Shadow and evil 'Yellow Eyes', even announcing their intent to 'cleanse' Crossport.

That forced Rand to confess to his family and seek support. Although shocked by the revelation, they were more concerned about his safety and sneaked him out of Crossport, claiming publicly that Rand went to start a business far, far away.

Now, Rand works as a lumberjack near Eversun. He can finally be himself. Alone in the woods without friends or family, he welcomes every visiting Gyee with passion.
